['Middlesex, before Mr. Sergeant Arabin.', "885.                \xa0                  JOSEPH                   BOWLEY                                                                                                             was indicted for that at the delivery of the King's gaol of Newgate, holden for Middlesex, at Justice-hall in the Old Bailey, on Thursday, the 6th of September, 3rd                \xa0                  William                   IV                                                                                       ., before certain Justices of our said Lord the King assigned to deliver the said gaol of the prisoners therein being, he the said                \xa0                  Joseph                   Bowley                                                                                        was in due form of law convicted, on his own confession, on a certain indictment against him, for feloniously stealing 1 piece of mahogany, value 10s.; 1 coffee-mill, value 5s.; 1 filterer, value 8s.; 10 candlesticks, value 1l.; 7 cocks, value 14s.; 3 tea-trays, value 6s.; 1 saucepan, value 8s.; 6 locks, value 18s.; 1 set of fire irons, value 12s.; 3 brushes, value 4s.; 2 hammers, value 1s.; 10 pounds weight of brass, value 1l.; 1 set of castors, value 2s.; 1 chain, value 4s.; 12 files, value 2s.; 40 gimblets, value 5s.; and 1 pair of scissors, value 1s. of                \xa0                  John                   Peachey                                                                                       , his master and employer, against the peace, &c.; and the said                \xa0                  Joseph                   Bowley                                                                                        was thereupon ordered to be transported beyond the seas for the term of seven years; and that he the said                \xa0                  Joseph                   Bowley                                                                                        afterwards, to wit, on the 25th of April                   last, at \xa0St. Margaret, Westminster                                                      ,                                                          feloniously was at large, without any lawful cause, before the expiration of the said term for which he was so ordered to be transported            ; against the Statute, &c. &c.", '2nd COUNT. The same as the first, only stating that at the said delivery of the gaol of Newgate, the said                \xa0                  Joseph                   Bowley                                                                                        was ordered to be transported beyond the seas for the term of seven years, and not setting out the offence; to which indictment he pleaded', '                                                                           GUILTY             -                                                          DEATH            . Aged 39.']